a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Kissflow is best suited for mid market companies, process owners, HR teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Process Street, meanwhile, shines for operations teams, onboarding, compliance, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Kissflow describes itself as \"Low-code work platform for process automation and project management.\" Process Street, established in 2014, positions itself as \"AI-powered workflow and checklist platform for recurring processes.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Process Street** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Kissflow is a poor choice — far from it. Kissflow excels in its own right, particularly for mid market companies and process owners.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent for documenting and running processes, go with Process Street. If combines workflow and project management matters more to you, Kissflow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
